title: Mount Black (Tasmania)
text:
Mount Black is a <a href="mountain">mountain</a> on the <a href="West%20Coast%20Range">West Coast Range</a> located in the <a href="West%20Coast%2C%20Tasmania">West Coast</a> region of <a href="Tasmania">Tasmania</a>, Australia. With an elevation of <a href="Australian%20Height%20Datum">above sea level</a>, the mountain is located adjacent to the town of <a href="Rosebery%2C%20Tasmania">Rosebery</a>.
The <a href="Murchison%20Highway">Murchison Highway</a> passes around its lower slopes.
It is the location of some former exploration and mine sites.
